    "body": "\r\n  ## Summary\r\n  - Improve the E77 error message to explain that glob expansion is unsupported in this command context.\r\n  - Update help text for the new wording.\r\n  - Add a functional test for `:edit` with a glob argument.\r\n\r\n  Closes #12139\r\n\r\n  ## Test\r\n  - `zig build functionaltest -- test/functional/ex_cmds/excmd_spec.lua`\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39843#discussion_r3255791070"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/39843"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3255791070"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "E77 is raised whenever a single-file command receives more than one file name, not exclusively from glob expansion. For example, `:edit file1 file2` (no wildcard) will also produce this error, and the new parenthetical \"(glob expansion is not supported here)\" will be misleading in that case. Consider wording that covers both cases, e.g. \"E77: Too many file names (only one allowed here)\", and keep the glob-specific guidance in the help text/hint rather than the error string. Additionally, modifying a long-standing Vim error message string can break user scripts, plugins, and translations that match on the exact text — worth confirming this trade-off is intentional.\n",
            "commit_id": "1ccf818373d659e4a285298b8e8760255d64f0ec",
            "created_at": "2026-05-18T00:44:33Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -118,7 +118,7 @@ EXTERN const char e_swapclose[] INIT(= N_(\"E72: Close error on swap file\"));\n EXTERN const char e_toocompl[] INIT(= N_(\"E74: Command too complex\"));\n EXTERN const char e_longname[] INIT(= N_(\"E75: Name too long\"));\n EXTERN const char e_toomsbra[] INIT(= N_(\"E76: Too many [\"));\n-EXTERN const char e_toomany[] INIT(= N_(\"E77: Too many file names\"));\n+EXTERN const char e_toomany[] INIT(= N_(\"E77: Too many file names (glob expansion is not supported here)\"));",
