            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "The explanatory paragraph below still says \\\"When expanding file names, more than one match was found\\\", which only describes the glob case. Since E77 can also fire for explicitly listed multiple file names, consider broadening this description (e.g., \\\"More than one file name was given (either explicitly or via glob expansion). Only one is allowed for the command that was used.\\\") so the help is consistent with all cases that raise the error.\n",
            "commit_id": "2651bcf83468f320d9def35d7e9b2b531f4192f3",
            "created_at": "2026-05-18T00:44:33Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -548,11 +548,13 @@ into this limit, you have used too many |:highlight| commands with different\n arguments.  A \":highlight link\" is not counted.\n \n \t\t\t\t\t\t\t*E77*  >\n-  Too many file names\n+  Too many file names (glob expansion is not supported here)\n \n When expanding file names, more than one match was found.  Only one match is\n allowed for the command that was used.",
